The paper deals with computer vision and natural language processing, which are both subfields of computer science. The use of Feature-wise Linear Modulation (FiLM) layers in convolutional networks suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also focuses on language input and multi-modal tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of FiLM layers for conditioning computation is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of visual dialogue. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
